    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A brief report in the Book Notes column on Wednesday omitted CBS's partners in the purchase of the American television rights to the novel "Scarlett." They are Robert Halmi, the chairman of RHI Entertainment Inc.; the Kirch Group, a German communications conglomerate, and Silvio Berlusconi, an Italian newspaper owner and broadcaster.</p>
      </block>
